HEADWORD: Edh
<hw>Edh</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The name of the
Anglo-Saxon letter ⟦edh⟧, capital form ⟦EDH⟧. It is sounded as
⟦ldquo⟧English <xex>th</xex> in a similar word: ⟦omac⟧⟦edh⟧er, other,
d⟦ocir⟧⟦edh⟧, doth.⟦rdquo⟧</def> <rj><au>March.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

